France,[IX] officially the French Republic,[X] is a country located
primarily in Western Europe. Its overseas regions and territories
include French Guiana in South America, Saint Pierre and Miquelon in the
North Atlantic, the French West Indies, and many islands in Oceania and
the Indian Ocean, giving it one of the largest discontiguous exclusive
economic zones in the world. Metropolitan France shares borders with
Belgium and Luxembourg to the north; Germany to the northeast.